-- Used by home page
[ last updated ]
for which V1 and _F1 is it true that
  ( the UI message V1 has the value _F1 as message text )
.

-- Used by list papers page
[ list papers ]
for which D is it true that
  ( there is a document named D )
.

-- Used by the OLD list papers page
[ document citations ]
for which V1, and V2 is it true that
  ( the document V1 has the paper citation count V2 as citation count )
.

-- Used by list authors page
[ list authors ]
for which P, PC and O is it true that
  ( the published person P has the person citation count PC as citation count ) and
  ( the published person P writes documents for the organisation O ) and
.

-- Used by the OLD list authors page
[ published person citations ]
for which V1, V2, V3, _F1 and _F2 is it true that
  ( the published person V1 has the person citation count V2 as citation count ) and
  ( the published person V1 writes documents for the organisation V3 ) and
  ( the published person V1 has the value _F1 as full name ) and
  ( the published person V1 has the value _F2 as document count )
.

-- Used by list venues page
[ event series ]
for which V1 and _F1 is it true that
  ( the published event series V1 has the value _F1 as full name ) and
  ( the published event series V1 has the value _F2 as paper count )
order by _F2 descending
.

-- Used by list organisations page
[ organisations ]
for which V1 is it true that
  ( there is a core organisation named V1 ) and
  ( the core organisation V1 is a published organisation )
.

-- Used by list topics page
[ topics ]
for which V1 is it true that
  ( there is a topic named V1 )
.

---- Used by list projects page (currently inactive)
--[ projects ]
--for which V1, V2 is it true that
--  ( the project V1 has the technical area V2 as technical area )
--.

-- Used by statistics page
[ totals ]
for which V1 is it true that
    ( there is a total named V1 )
.

-- Used by event details page
[ event series details ]
for which V1, V2, V3, V4, V5, V6, V7, V8  is it true that
  ( the document V1 has the event V3 as venue ) and
  ( the document V1 has the paper citation count V8 as citation count ) and
  ( the published person V2 wrote the document V1 ) and
  ( the published person V2 writes documents for the organisation V5 ) and
  ( the event V3 is part of the event series V4 ) and
  ( the event V3 occurs at the place V7 ) and
  ( the organisation V5 is located at the place V6 ) and
.

-- Used by co-authors wheel page (1 of 5)
[ organisation details ]
for which O, ON, SN, OT and C is it true that
  ( the published organisation O has the value ON as name ) and
  ( the published organisation O is a core organisation ) and
  ( the published organisation O has the value SN as short name ) and
  ( the published organisation O has the value OT as type ) and
  ( the published organisation O is affiliated to the country C )
.

-- Used by co-authors wheel page (2 of 5)
[ person details ]
for which P, FN, SN, TC and CC is it true that
  ( the published person P has the value FN as forename ) and
  ( the published person P is a core person ) and
  ( the published person P has the value SN as surname ) and
  ( the published person P has the value TC as document count ) and ( the value TC > '0' ) and
  ( the published person P has the value CC as co-author count ) and ( the value CC > '0' )
order by TC, CC descending
.

-- Used by co-authors wheel page (3 of 5)
[ published person -> organisation ]
for which P and O is it true that
  ( the published person P writes documents for the organisation O ) and
  ( the published person P is a core person ) and
  ( the published person P has the value C as co-author count ) and ( the value C > '0' )
.

-- Used by co-authors wheel page (4 of 5)
[ person -> document ]
for which P and AD is it true that
  ( the published person P wrote the document AD ) and
  ( the published person P is a core person ) and
  ( the published person P has the value C as co-author count ) and ( the value C > '0' )
.

-- Used by co-authors wheel page (5 of 5)
[ document details ]
for which AD and T is it true that
  ( the document AD has the value T as title )
.
